title: Extension of the energy range of the experimental activation cross-sections data of longer-lived products of proton induced nuclear reactions on dysprosium up to 65 MeV

activation cross-sections data of longer-lived
products of proton induced nuclear reactions on
dysprosium up to 65 MeV

x4freetext: Natural dysprosium foil, thickness: 22.1 microns
A stack containing
natural Dy foils as target, natural Ti foils as
monitor foils and Al foils as energy degraders were
irradiated with a proton beam of 65 MeV, 25 nA for
1 hour.
Gamma spectra were measured nondestructively in
4 series with cooling time intervals: 22-31.6 h,
Chapter 4
The uncertainty of the beam energy in the
middle of each irradiated foil was estimated
combining the uncertainties of the energy degradation
depending on the thickness of the target foils in the
stack and the energy straggling. The uncertainty of the
initial beam energy was +/-0.3 MeV and 0.8 MeV for the
last Dy foil in the stack.
The uncertainty on the cross-section was
estimated by taking the square root of the sum in
quadrature of all individual contributions, supposing
equal sensitivities for the different parameters.
The main error components:
surface density of target nuclei (5%)
incident charged particle flux (8%)
detector efficiency  (5%)
nuclear data (5%)
statistical uncertainty (1.-15.%)
Fitted excitation functions were used for
determination of integral physical yields.
